'''kilo-'''
#In the [[International System of Units]] and other [[metric]] systems of units, multiplying the [[unit]] to which it is attached by 1,000. Symbol: k

====Etymology====
From {{F.}}, irregular from {{Gr.}} '''[[chilioi]]''', ''thousand''. The "correct" form would be '''chili-''', resulting in forms such as '''chiliogram''' and '''chiliometer'''. In fact, one such form (lacking the connecting vowel '''-o-''', which is explained at [[Hippopotomonstrosesquippedaliophobia]]) used to exist in English: '''[[chilihedron]]''', meaning a thousand-faced solid.

